column9: Summary
Reposition Hallco mast unit from SA - to SA-22. R/U mast unit to support slickline job.
R/U Slickline, presure test PCE 250/2000 psi 5 minutes - OK. RIH with 3" GS pulling tool, latch and retrieve flapper valve @ depth 478'. POH.
M/U 2.72" TGC tools, RIH to HUD @ 12.230' WLM POH and R/D Slickline unit.
R/U Mast Unit. M/U RMT-EU - Capacitance tools. Perform surface calibration and test on Q-test sub.
RIH RMT Tools @ 100 FPM, stop at depth 3100' due to high inclination.
POH tools, Line up pump hose to Hallco pumping tee. Attempted to pump while RIH with rate up to 2 BPM 1400 psi but unsuccessful to get the RMT tool pass thru high dog leg at 3100'.
POOH RMT tools. Added roller into toolstring.

RIH RMT tools with roller to HUD 3500' pumped up to 6 BPM 850 psi tools moved down 50' FPM to 12,235'. Correlate depth with open hole log. 

Total FSW4%KCL pumped 958 bbls.
Pull up with logging speed 10 fpm and start to record 1st pulse neutron log data from depth 12,200' to 10,550'.

RIH RMT Tools with sped 50 FPM and pump rate 4 BPM to 12,200'. 

Total Fluid injected 203 bbls
Pick up with logging speed 10 fpm and start to record 2nd pulse neutron log data from depth 12,200' to 10,550'.
Continue POH RMT tools to surface.

L/D Hallco lubricator and perform housekeeping.

Final report of Serang SA-22 RMT logging on Dec 31, 2012 at 06:00 hrs.

Commencing operation on Serang - 22.
MTR- Barge under towed from Attaka Barfo Platform to Attaka Serang Platform.

BOP stump test:
1. Blind ram#3, inside CK manual#5, valve 8, 14, 16	: 300/3000 psi 10 mts.
2. Blind ram#3, inside CK manual#5, valve 8, 9, 11, 12, 16	: 300/3000 psi 10 mts.
3. Blind ram#3, valve 8, 10, 11, 12, 16			: 300/3000 psi 10 mts.
4. VBR#2, kill valve#6, valve 8, 9, 11, 13, 16, TIW#18	:  300/3000 psi 10 mts.
5. VBR#2, kill valve#7, valve 9, 10,11,14,16, TIW valve#18	:  300/3000 psi 10 mts.
6. Annular#1, Manual#5, Valve 8, 14, 16, TIW#18		:  300/3000 psi 10 mts.
7. VBR#1, Valve 8, 9, 11, 13, 16. TIW valve#18		:  300/3000 psi 10 mts.
Towing from Attaka Brafo Platform to Attaka Serang Platform.
AHT T. Attaka and Kittiwake ran and dropped all anchors.
Cross tension test anchor wires to 38 Klbs. Good test.
Moved barge to final position with 341.5 degree heading.
Installed gangway and ESD control line.
Inspected platform and SIMOP meeting.
R/U pumping line while wait on E-line operation on well Serang SA-26.

Run RMT Sigma logging program.

Suspend tubing repair operation to perform logging operation on Dec 29, 2012 at 18:00 hrs.
RU Slickline lubricator with mast and pressure test to 300/2500 psi. RIH reset flapper SCSSV at 478' nipple. R/D slickline lubricator and mast unit. Set BPV.
Arranged space & picked up gangway by production crane to top deck for construction crew repairing socket.

Offloaded Koommy and Elnusu equipment to top deck. 

Instruction from town to postpone Serang SA-22 recompletion program.
Operation suspended until tbg AOL.
Production bleed down G/L line & flowline. Moved equip on top deck. Moved Halliburton mast unit to MTR-1. Moved koomey unit & power pack to top deck. Cleaned production top deck.
RU SL and Elnusa HP lines from pump manifold to SL side-entry pump-in sub & csg valve. Test lines to 300/3000 psi. Test lub from 300/3000 psi.
RIH & pull flapper valve @ 478'.
Bleed 500 psi tbg pressure to 0 psi, bleed 850 psi on csg to 0 psi. Pump down tbg 243 bbl FSW w/ 3% KCL. Filled up csg w/ FSW+3% KCL.
Continue fill up csg w/ 587 bbl of FSW+3%KCl.
RIH slickline & re-set flapper valve at 478'. RD slickline.
Press test tbg hanger cavity to 300/3000 psi. Set BPV. Remove production choke & isolate w/ blind flange.
ND X-tree. Install test plug & control line plug.
NU 11" 5M riser & 11" 5M BOP stack.
Test riser & blind rams to 300/3000 psi on a chart. Good Test.

Safety Stand Down Meeting. Reviewed iCU cards on texting while walking down stairs, poor housekeeping & proper cell phone usage...to be treated as a non-explosion proof equipment....to be used only in the stern of the MTR-1 behind the living quarters.
Continued RU Elnusa 225 unit. RU window, jacks & workbasket. Secured w/ guide wires.

Safety Stand Down Meeting. Reviewed iCU cards on texting while walking down stairs, poor housekeeping & proper cell phone usage...to be treated as a non-explosion proof equipment....to be used only in the stern of the MTR-1 behind the living quarters.
Continued RU Elnusa 225 unit. RU window, jacks & workbasket. Secured w/ guide wires. RU gin pole, tong arm, power tong, control console and hoses.
Continue function test snubbing unit, install 6" return line, offload standpipe.landing joint.mouse hole and 4-1/2" tubing for BOP annular test.
Pressure test 4-1/2" pipe ram to 300/3000 psi and Annular BOP with 4-1/2" tubing inside to 300/1500 psi, hold for 5 minutes each, OK.
Fill up tubing with 10 bbls 3% KCL to ensure no press trap below BPV. Pull out BPV
RU slickline lub/safety valve to landing jt/TIW in work basket. Tested lub. Replaced o-rings & retested lub 300/3000 psi.
MU pulling tool & pull flapper valve @ 478'.
MU shifting tool w/ roller stem.  RIH & toolstring stopped going in hole @ 6600' (71* deviation). Pumped toolstring downhole (1-1/2 bpm) & opened SSD at 9546'. POOH. RD slickline.
RU Halliburton unit. MU safety valve &  lub to TIW valve in workbasket. Test lub to 300/3000 psi.
MU GPWP toolstring. RIH & found fluid level @ 1050', 9000' MD, BHP 1724 psi, 180*F, POOH.

MU 2-3/8" tbg cutter. RIH & tool stopped @ 3372' (71* deveation). Pumped toolstring downhole @ 1 bpm.Tool stop @6800' (72* deviation) Pumped  toolstring downhole @1.5 bpm total fluid pumped to hole 126 bbls with no return. Correlate to tbg details(got stuck on 9550' suspect centralizer stuck on the XD sleeve profile, work string up/down several time get free), Cut tbg @ 9500'. POOH. RD Halliburton EL unit.

Pull hanger and tbg free10ft at 68 Klbs. Pump 300 bbls @ 3 bpm 250 psi, return mixed oil gas and water. Circulate clean while make up transfer line to production facility. Observe well static while waiting for transfer line completed.
Transfer oil 80 bbls to production facility with 0.75 bpm @220 psi.flush line, fill up tubing to ensure no more gas or oil from string with 60 bbls return clean water.

Pulled tubing hanger, control line and 3-1/2" completion string to surface while continue fill up with105 bbls to get return, break out tubing hanger on work basket. Pump 2 bpm to get returns @ surface. Formation taking completion fluid @ 1 bpm.
TOH w/ old 3-1/2" completion string. Rolling mud pump @ 0.4 bpm while TOH. Commulative 3-1/2" tubing pull out 296 jnts plus 17' tubing cut, 6 SPM and 1 BVN.Bundling tubing and offload to MTR1 deck.

Offload all old completion string to MTR1 deck and pick up Five 3-1/2" NSCT tubing jts and completion accessories to top deck (ltail pipe below packer). Set 2.81" PX Plug body and prong at surface in the 2.81" X landing nipple.
Conduct JSA meeting to discuss run completion and combination string, how to handle and lift the tubular properly.
Start RIH 3-1/2" NSCT Mule shoe, 1 jnt tubing ,X landing nipple and 1 jnt tubing with PX Plug body and prong set inside.
Installed PX plug in lower X Nipple at surface deck. Pressure test PX Plug body and prong to 4000 psi hold for 5 minutes OK. Schlumberger drifted all jewelry on location.
Continue TIH 9-5/8" MRP Packer followed by 3-1/2' NSCT tubing, XD Sleeve(jar up to open) and bottom SPM. Drifted ea. jt as run.
Transfer 94 ea, 4-1/2" 13.5# C95 13Cr Vam Top to top deck  and tally pipe.

Continue TIH w/ 4-1/2" 13.5#, C-95, 13Cr, Vam Top completion tbg 88 jnts (3711 ft). Fill tbg w/ FSW w/ 3% KCL every 5 jts while TIH. Continue rolling mud pump @ 0.4 bpm for well control (TOF @ +/-1050'). Drifted ea. jt as run.

Continue TIH w/ 4-1/2" 13.5#, C-95, 13Cr, Vam Top completion tbg. Fill tbg w/ FSW w/ 3% KCL every 5 jts while TIH. Continue rolling mud pump @ 0.4 bpm for well control (TOF @ +/-1050'). All completion jewelries and tbg run in to the hole were drifted.
Transfer 61 ea tubing 4-1/2" 12.6# L-80 Vam Top to top deck and tally pipe.

Continue TIH w/ 4-1/2" 12.6#, L-80, Vam Top completion tbg drifting each jt, Fill tbg w/ FSW w/ 3% KCL every 5 jts while TIH. Continue rolling mud pump @ 0.4 bpm for well control (TOF @ +/-1050'). All completion jewelries run in to the hole were drifted.
MU 4-1/2" TRSV. Tested control line/TRSV to 5000 psi for 5 minutes.

Continue TIH w/ 4-1/2" 12.6#, L-80, Vam Top completion tbg drifting each jt, Fill tbg w/ FSW w/ 3% KCL every 5 jts while TIH. Strapping TRSV control line to tbg. Continue rolling mud pump @ 0.4 bpm for well control.
MU FMC hanger. MU TRSV control line. Test TRSV to 5000 psi. Land hanger. Test top side of hanger to 500 psi. Energize pack-off & set hanger. Pull test hanger 10K overpull (59K pipe wt, pulled 69K).

Attempted to set 9-5/8" MRP packer. Pumped 12 bbl before seeing pressure in tbg. Pressure tbg to 500 psi & bled off in 40 sec to 200 psi several times taking 1 bbl to repressure tbg. Pressured tbg to 1000 psi w/ same results. Leak/communication in tbg ( 4 SPM, SSD tested in SLB shop & PX plug below packer tested in workbasket). Called for slickline crew.
Wait on slickline crew to arrive on location to find leak in completion string.
Discussed w/ slickline plan of attack for finding & fixing communication in tbg.
RU slickline in workbasket in TIW valve. Tested lub to 300/3000 psi.
RIH w/ 3.5" catcher sub,tool string tagged up at 5286' wlm (SPM @ 5229' MD), try to pass several times w/ no success, pooh same,change tool string composition.
RIH w/ Pony tail to find leaking point, tagged up @ 5286'  without finding communication above 5286', try to pass several times w/o success, pooh.
MU 2.6" IB. RIH w/ 2.60" IB to 5286 ft wlm & tagged up, Pooh, No mark on IB.
MU 2.27" IB. RIH to get an immpression @ 5286' wlm. Tagged @ 5286' & POH. Same mark of metal surface (look like crossover).
Change tool string composition and MU 2.6" IB.  RIH & slid pass 5286' (no tag) & tagged up @  6381' wlm. Attempted to work pass 6381' slm w/o success. POH. No mark on IB.

MU pony tail on last toolstring(1-7/8" rope socket + 1-7/8" x 5 ft stem + 1-7/8" x 3ft roller stem + knuckle joint + 1-7/8" x 3 ft roller stem + 1-7/8" spang jar + pony tail ). RIH to look for leak point. Tagged up @ 6381' SPM. Could not work past SPM. POH.
Shut down due to bad weather.

MU PX plug. RIH to set in SSD profile. Could not run past SSD @ 6379' slm (run past & PU to Profile to set PX plug). POH & RD slickline. Talked to office, decided to pull completion string to find problem.
PU landing jt & latch hanger. Unset hanger & PU same, 60K to pull hanger free (tbg wt 59K). Break out hanger & lay down same. Disconnect TRSV control line from hanger & pump TRSV open.

TOH w/ 4-1/2"  completion string spooling TRSV control line. Break out & lay down 4-1/2" TRSV. Tested tbg below TRSV, pumped 12 bbl before pressure built to 200 psi. Tested tbg to 400 psi and pressure dropped to 200 psi in 1 minute. Kept mud pump rate @ 0.4 bpm for well control while TOH.

Continue TOH w/ 4-1/2" completion string testing tbg to 300/400 psi @ jt #39, #50, #76,(pump 12 bbls to get press 400 psi in 1 minutes drop to 200 psi) #84. Kept mud pump rate @ 0.4 bpm for well control while TOH.
Continue TOH w/ 4-1/2" completion string  tbg to jnt # 84
Continue TOH w/ 4-1/2" completion string testing tbg to 400 psi at jnt#88,12 bbls pumped to get 400 psi. 1 minute drop to 200 psi.
Continue TOH w/ 4-1/2" completion string to jnt#93 (wet string) test tubing to 400 psi & drop to 100 psi in 1 minute. Found several bad jt conn on the 4-1/2" 13.5# C95 13 CrVam Top tbg.

RU SL. Test lub 300/2000 psi. RIH w/ SST & check SSD to ensure closed. Tagged @ SSD, could not run through SSD. Found 3/8" impression on IB face about 3/8" from outer edge of IB. Cleaned IB. Reran w/ same results. Looks like something is across/inside SSD preventing slickline tool from running through SSD.

Continue TOH w/ 4-1/2" completion string. Found several bad jt conn of 4-1/2" 13.5# C95 13Cr Vam Top tbg. Tested tbg @ tbg jt #111, Pumped 0.3 bbl to pressure tbg to 400 psi, 2 minutes for tbg to bleed to 200 psi. Tested tbg @ jt #125 (on top of #2 SPM) w/ same leak results.

Moved one row of 4-1/2" 13.5# C95 13Cr Vam Top tbg from pipe rack on top deck to MTR-1. Pipe was getting too high and Tuboscope can do a better job checking pipe threads without pipe coming down out of the workbasket .

Continue TOH w/ 4-1/2" completion string. Pulling 4-1/2" 13.5# C95 13Cr Vam Top tbg. Tested tbg @ tbg jt #151 on top of SPM #1 plus 1 jnt 3-1/2" Pumped 0.3 bbl to pressure tbg to 400 psi, 2 minutes for tbg to bleed to 200 psi. Note: Jt# 151 was the last jt of 4-1/2" 13Cr tbg.
Continue TOH w/ 3-1/2" completion string,1 jnt above SSD tested to 400 psi, holding good test. Continue pull out string and MRP packer, 1 jnt 3-1/2" plus X landing nipple w/PX plug and prong inside.
Standby due to very high wind speed and heavy rain.
Continue arrange 4-1/2" 13 Cr tubing to the booster.
Shut down due to weather.
Continue arrange 4-1/2" 13 Cr tubing to the booster.
Off-loaded  9-5/8" retrievable packer from boat. BJ Service tech inspected the packer & storm valve. Safety meeting with BJ & Elnusa on running & setting the packer.

PU & ran 9-5/8" retrievable packer w/ storm valve to 1046' (fluid depth). Set packer. Slacked off 100% tbg wt on packer. Pull tested to packer to15K. Released from packer & PU tbg 5'. Filled annulus & tested packer to 500 psi. TOH w/ 3-1/2" tbg. Closed blind rams and tested packer to 1500 psi.

PU & TIH w/ 10 jts of kill string. MU hanger. RIH & landed. Pressure test hanger seal to 500 psi. Energized hanger and pull test to 10Klbs over. Released running tool & pulled landing jts. MU BPV. Ran same & set in hanger. Laid down landing jts. Back load 4 bundles of 4-1/2" Vam top tubing from pipe rack to MTR-1 deck.
Held PJSM with EWS & Barge crew; review JSA R/D SNB 225 unit.
Scoop down gin pole, while pumping approx 50 bbls of oil from EWS tank to production thru SA-29 well.
Disconnected hydraulic hoses. R/D hydraulic equipment and prepare for R/D work basket at report time.
Continued to R/D SNB 225.

N/D 11" x 5K BOP and 11" x 5M riser.

Note:
Daily 3% KCl-FSW pumped to the well (00.00 - 15.00 hrs) = 360 bbls.
Installed test plug in hanger. NU tree. Installed blind flanges on tree. Tested tree to 300/3000 psi. Pulled test plug.

RD hoses from csg & swab valve.
Operations suspended at 11.00 on 17 January 2013, until 4-1/2" tbg is located & transported to location.

Con't to tow Tirta Samudera barge to clear area outer bar, Balikpapan on anchor line #5 & hold on #8 with AHVS Temasek Sepinggan & Pioneer 4. Payout 200 meter anchor line #5 to re spool correctly to winch, hold steady on #8 anchor line. Connect tow bridle to Temasek Sepinggan & release anchor line #8 from Pioneer 4
Receive basket from Peacock Dua with X-over's to allow EWS to test BOP variable rams. Lift Yokohama fenders  from Port & Starboard sides & stow on deck
Commence towing with Temasek Sepinggan to Serang platform @ average 3.0 knots.
Con't towing to Serang platform with Temasek Sepinggan. 41NM to Serang platform with average speed 2.6 - 3.2 knots
Con't towing to Serang platform with Temasek Sepinggan. 16NM to Serang platform with average speed 2.6 - 3.2 knots
Con't towing to Serang platform with Temasek Sepinggan @ average 2.0 knots. 2.0NM to Serang platform

Start anchor handling, pull out anchor line #1 with Pioneer 4 & hold barge. Temasek Sepinggan disconnect tow bridle & pick up anchor line #5. (TS) pull anchor line c/w pennant lines & run anchor to drop point. pick up pennant lines & anchor line #4 with (TS) & run anchor to drop point, (TS) pick up pennant lines & anchor line #8 & run anchor to drop point. (P4) run anchor #1 to drop point, 

(TS) Temasek Sepinggan, (P4) Pioneer 4

Pick up pennant lines & run anchors to drop position #6 (TS), #3 (P4), #2 (P4) & #7 (P4)

(TS) Temasek Sepinggan, (P4) Pioneer 4.

Note: Buoy #7 sink. Plan to replace the buoy on day light.
Standby wait on gangway socket modification on platform. Pre tension all anchors to 10 - 12 T.
Con't wait on gangway socket & pad eyes installation on Serang platform.
Pioneer 4 attempt to recover buoy at #7 anchor, no success buoy is 5 meter below sea level. Notify all vessels of under water hazard at coordinates. Con't to stand by on socket & pad eyes
Socket arrived to platform @ 16:00. All dims of gangway sent to production/construction.
Con't wait on gangway socket & pad eyes installation on Serang platform.
Stand by wait on gangway socket installation.
Stand by wait on gangway socket installation. Construction start install/weld @ 08:00
Stand by wait on gangway socket installation @ 18:00 80% complete, pad eyes 0%
Stand by wait on gangway socket installation.
Stand by on gangway socket install & MPI
Welding of gangway socket complete. Con't with pad eyes & allow the welds to cool prior to MPI
All welding complete & MPI of socket & pad eyes passed inspection
Pull barge into final position 10.5 meter from platform on anchor lines. Tension anchor lines 11.0 - 17.0 ton.

Remove handrail on stern of barge. Pick up gangway with crane & install to socket on platform. Install safety lines from platform pad eyes to gangway. Secure all openings around gangway on barge & platform.

Note: Gangway very steep at high tide. BMB prepare to make Mud Dog 1.0 - 1.5 meter high to go under gangway to reduce angle as tide goes out.
Connect ESD line. P/U portable lighting & eye wash station to top deck. Install lighting.
Offload work basket to top deck to make space for food container on barge's deck. Test tbg hanger cavity to 300/3000 psi for 5/10 mins. OK. P/U 2" & 6" hoses to top deck.
R/U surface line for csg and tbg. N/D Choke body and Wing valve & install blind flange.
Press test Csg line to 300/2000 psi for 5/5 min's. OK. Press test Tbg line to 300/3500 psi for 5/5 min's. OK.
Open well. SI TP = 0 psi. CP = 100 psi. Bleed off all pressure through choke manifold to zero. Monitor well stable. Set BPV.
Offload power pack, Koomey, hoses from barge to top deck. Alongside LCT Hamota 0. Offload riser from Hamota 0 to top deck.
M/U riser correct length on top deck. While transfer 225 equipments from Hamota 0 to top deck.
Install test plug.
N/D X-Mas tree. Install blind flange on flowline. Lift X-Mas tree to top deck.
N/U riser & clamp to wellhead.
Cut BOP Press skid off of deck & lift c/w 11" BOP & Annular to top deck. Change to platform crane, land BOP on riser & N/U.
Connect BOP & Annular control hoses & function rams. R/U 2" 1502 pump line top deck to kill line & 6" hose to stack.
Press test line 300/3,500 psi 5-5 min's. Close Blind rams press test 300/3,000 psi 5-5 min's against test plug.

R/U EWS 225 unit complete and function test system.

Note: Lift EWS 225 components to platform deck with barge crane then R/U with platform crane due to barge movement 2-3 deg roll
Offload pipe rack, landing joint and running tool to top deck.
Held prejob meeting prior to POH tbg hanger & kill string and RIH work string to retrieve RBP.
Pull test plug.
Pull BPV. M/U landing joint. Pull tbg hanger pack off.
Screw landing joint to tbg hanger. Pull tbg hanger free & L/D same. Fill up annulus until get return after 8 bbl's.
POOH 10 Jnt's of 3-1/2" NSCT kill string. Fill up annulus until get return after 5 bbl's.

Offload 4-1/2" Hydril 563 tbg from LCT Hamota II to barge. Backload NSCT tbg ex-well to barge. Offload 40 Jnt's of 3-1/2" TKC work string to top deck. While SLB crew M/U new completion assembly on barge's deck. Drift assembly with 2.80" drift.
Lay TKC tbg on pipe rack, remove thread protector & tally pipe.
M/U BJ RBP retrieving tool. RIH same on 3-1/2" TKC tbg.
Con't TIH 3-1/2" TKC Tbg. Csg & Tbg press 0 psi.

Stop 10' above 9-5/8" RBP @ 1,036' MD make up Kelly hose & pump sub. Press test line 300/3,000 psi  5-5 min's.
Start circulate down Tbg 20 bbl's, returns at choke.

TIH tag RBP @ 07:40 press below RBP release from well & TKC work string ejected out of well, water followed by oil. At 07:45 Blind rams closed all work string blown out of well. All persons in basket accounted for & no injury. Csg press 400 psi at choke.
Raise alarm on barge & muster all personnel. All persons accounted for & all persons returned from platform. Notify town of the incident, all personnel no injury.

Monitor well press at choke increase to 760 psi. Assess situation on platform & barge for damage. All 3-1/2" TKC work string blown out. Work String hanging from counterbalance line & Kelly hose approx 30' from platform deck, work string over side of platform to sea & back up over gangway & starboard side of TS barge to sea. Gangway main frame bent & handrails bent over. Snubbing unit, operator cover  bent, stand pipe & Kelly hose. Require to inspect unit once well killed & work string secured.

Equalize press at choke 760 psi, start pumping filtered sea water @ 1.0 bpm, 800 psi. 25 bbls pumped inc to 2.0 bpm, 800 psi. At 41 bbls pumped inc to 3.0 bpm, 750-800 psi. 100 bbls pumped press 700 psi, 131 bbls press 650 psi.

Con't bullhead filter sea water @ 3.0 bpm. At 200 bbl's inc to 3.2 bpm, 600 psi. At 280 bbl's, 400 psi, at 316 bbl's, 300 psi, at 387 bbl's, 250 psi, at 464 bbl's, 300 psi, at 500 bbl's stop pump & monitor. Choke press 190 psi. Bleed off slowly at gas buster, only fluid returns & press inc to 300 psi. Close choke & line up to con't well kill.
Con't pumping filter sea water @ 3.2 bpm, 400 psi, at 608 bbl's, 400 psi. at 682 bbl's 200 psi. Stop pumping 700 bbl's, 100 psi. Monitor at choke.
Monitor Csg press at choke, start 220 psi, at 15:00 choke press 500 psi.

Bleed down press slowly via choke & gas buster, press inc to 550 psi before slowly decrease. At 15:30 500 psi, at 15:45 320 psi, at 16:00 200 psi. Gas, oil & water return at gas buster. Shut in choke & line up to Con't well kill.

Line up & Con't bull head filter sea water @ 3.0 bpm. At 16:50 824 bbl's 130 psi, at 17:30 938 bbl's 100 psi, at 18:00 1,055 bbl's 80 psi, 18:40 1,173 bbl's, at 19:00 1,234 psi, at 19:15 1,250 bbls. Stop pump & monitor on choke.
Monitor Csg press at choke, at 19:15 30 psi, at 19:45 100 psi, at 20:15 160 psi.

Bleed down press slowly via choke & gas buster, bleed off water & gas from 160 psi. At 60 psi start to see oil in returns. Shut in at choke press inc to 70 psi. Monitor Csg press at choke, at 21:30 160 psi, at 21:45 180 psi.
Bleed down press slowly via choke & gas buster, bleed off water & gas from 160 psi. At 90 psi start to see liquid in returns. Shut in at choke at 22:10 hrs press 90 psi.

Block ESD from platform to barge since ESD line closed to gangway. Close 2" casing valve on well by Production crew since the weather get worse, the pumping line just below gangway. Casing line 160 psi, bleed off to 0 psi. At 23:30 hrs Production team disconnect control line. Monitor on weather condition.
Monitor weather condition and observe barge situation. Hold PTSM & discuss forward plan to kill well & recover work string. Hold OE meeting, Barge mechanic to inspect crane for damage.
Discuss status with office & EWS crew, forward plan to kill well, mix KCL & platform inspection.
Hold PJM with personnel for move  manually KCL sacks & mixing of 3% FSW KCL. Also discuss for platform inspection by EWS to assess condition & for forward plan to recover work string.
Csg valve leaking, choke press @ 300 psi, at 08:45 335 psi, at 09:00 350 psi.

Start to manual lift KCL sacks to top of mix tank using cloth strops. Crew travel to platform on crew boat & start inspection of top deck with production operator. Open Csg valves to choke, press 360 psi, close Csg valves & grease. MI Swaco unit not starting @ 10:00, fault find problem with barge mechanic.

MI unit started req 120 psi for starter, start to mix 500 bbl's of 3% FSW KCL. 
EWS crew re route Csg & Tbg pump lines above ejected work string to Con't pumping & monitor press at choke.

Line up Csg valves open against choke. press 400 psi. Start pumping 3% KCL 1.0 bpm 400 psi, Inc. to 3 bpm @ 500 psi.
15:00, 260 bbl's, 180 psi, 3 bpm
15:45, 405 bbl's, 80 psi, 3 bpm
16:15, 500 bbl's 20 psi, stop pumping
Monitor Csg press at choke. At 16:30, press 85 psi. At 20:30, press 360 psi. Line up kill line to choke manifold.
Pre job meeting with crews for line up kill line, mixing fluid and pump fluid and bleed off.
Press test kill line to 300/3000 psi for 5/10 mins. OK.
Initial press 370 psi. Start pumping FSW 1 BPM from csg line. Bleed off gas pressure from kill line through choke manifold to gas buster 5 psi / minute.

Pumping FSW 1 BPM from Csg line. Bleed off gas pressure from kill line through choke manifold to gas buster 5 psi / minute. Pumping pressure 15 psi. Kill line 0 psi. Stop pump after122 bbl's pumped. Monitor well pressure. 
00:30 hrs 15 psi. 
01:00 hrs 25 psi.
01:30 hrs 60 psi.
02:00 hrs 90 psi.
02:30 hrs 100 psi.
03:00 hrs 140 psi.
03:30 hrs 180 psi.
04:00 hrs 210 psi.
04:30 hrs 240 psi.

Con't to monitor Csg press, at 09:30, 240 psi, at 13:00 ,390 psi.
Waiting on construction personnel to arrive for securing of work string & cutting.
At 14:00 press 400 psi. Wait on construction to arrive for securing of work string & cutting.
Hold PJM with EWS crew to connect clamps to work string & disconnect Kelly hose & counter balance line.
